mber of observations.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EIn this case: (120 + 118 + 122 + 142 + 125 + 119 + 121 + 117) \u00f7 8 = 984 \u00f7 8 = \u003Cstrong\u003E123 mmHg\u003C/strong\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003ENote that the mean (123 mmHg) is pulled higher than most individual values due to the presence of one high value (142 mmHg), demonstrating how the mean is sensitive to extreme values in a dataset.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":null,"learningPoints":["The arithmetic mean is the sum of all observations divided by the number of observations.","The mean is sensitive to extreme values (outliers) in a dataset.","The mean represents the balance point or center of mass of a distribution."],"references":["Sullivan LM. Essentials of biostatistics in public health. 3rd ed. Burlington (MA): Jones \u0026 Bartlett Learning; 2018.","Dawson B, Trapp RG. Basic \u0026 clinical biostatistics. 4th ed. New York: McGraw-Hill; 2004."]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"55749"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"17390"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"55749","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/55749"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2024-12-14T11:05:41+10:30","updatedAt":"2024-12-14T11:07:14+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"10080"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"70285"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"67","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/67"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Basic Science","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"5"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"71","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/71"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Junior","synonyms":null,"description":"Suitable for a junior, pre-clinical medica